txt.en: DNT - Blah!

By locking gates to other parts of Goblin-town, you can keep under control the number of goblins with which you must contend.\n\n<rgb=#FF0000>Stay on the upper level! If you fall to the lower levels you will be swiftly defeated.</rgb>
'You have done well to hinder the goblins, but even so we cannot hope for Bilbo to be unguarded. We must act quickly!'
<rgb=#FF0000>Do not fall down to the lower level!</rgb>
Now that it is (relatively) safe, Celeblír has arrived.
Goblins howl with frustration as you close the gate
Harsh curses echo off the tunnel walls as you lock the gate
Wait for Celeblír to arrive
The heavy gate swings closed, muffling sounds of rage from beyond
Goblin-town will be full of the creatures, but if you act quickly you might be able to slow them down by locking the gates to other parts of the city.
'Well done, [placeholder]!'
The Guardian of the Jails has arrived, and he is not pleased to see you.\n\n<rgb=#FF0000>Stay on the upper level! If you fall to the lower levels you will be swiftly defeated.</rgb>
A booming voice heralds the arrival of the Guardian of the Jails!
'What's all this?'
'Who's shutting the gates in my city?'
'That's MY job!'
'No one!'
Mission: The Further Adventures of Bilbo Baggins, Chapter 8
'If you think you're saving your little friend, you're more stupid than you look! No one escapes from Goblin-town!'
